**Category:** essay-draft truth lindbeck caputo faith convictions practical-knowledge ontological-truth

**Abstract:**
Essay titled "After Truth" examining what remains after abandoning the contemplative paradigm of truth. Opens with quotations from McInerny and Marshall on Lindbeck. Argues practical convictions guide action without corresponding to reality as pictures. Distinguishes from Lindbeck by frankly denying ontological truth while clarifying this doesn't entail God's non-existence. Critiques Caputo's deconstructionism.

**AI Recommendation:** Major theoretical essay on post-foundationalist faith; see 98-FEB-1-1 variant.

